article.description: — Kendric Davis had 18 points in Memphis' 87-68 win over North Alabama on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Memphis wins 87-68 against North Alabama
article.story: MEMPHIS, Tenn. -- — Kendric Davis had 18 points in Memphis' 87-68 win over North Alabama on Wednesday night. Davis shot 4 for 7 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 8 of 8 from the free throw line for the Tigers (5-2). DeAndre Williams scored 15 points while going 7 of 9 from the field. Keonte Kennedy recorded 11 points and was 5 of 14 shooting (1 for 5 from distance). The Lions (4-4) were led by Daniel Ortiz with 16 points. KJ Johnson added 10 points and five assists for North Alabama. Dallas Howell scored eight points. Memphis led North Alabama 46-28 at the half, with Davis scoring 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
